The paper deals with graph theory and combinatorial optimization, which are topics covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. The concept of pairwise compatibility graphs is related to distance geometry, which is a topic covered by cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also deals with the analysis of subclasses of pairwise compatibility graphs, which is related to computational geometry, a topic covered by cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also discusses split matrogenic graphs, which are a subclass of intersection graphs, a topic covered by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the intersection and union of subclasses of pairwise compatibility graphs, which is related to graph theory and combinatorics, topics covered by cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
